==English==

===Alternative forms===
* yo momma
* yer maw
* yer ma

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[your]] [[mom]]|-}}

# Used as a riposte and often as a counter-riposte to an insulting statement (and recently, even to non-insulting statements).
#:''You're an idiot.''
#:'''''Your mom''' is an idiot!''

====Usage notes====
Sometimes used to skew another person's words or as a [[non sequitur]]:

:''Ramen noodles are cheap and easy.''
:'''''Your mom''' is cheap and easy!''

This use of "your mom" is different from ''[[w:The dozens|the dozens]]'' in that no response is expected from the first person, as "your mom" builds off of the original sentence. It is not a contest but a one-time retort.

The phrase is sometimes used as a complete sentence:
:''You're an idiot.''
:''Yo momma!''

====Quotations====
* '''2004,''' ''[[w:Napoleon Dynamite|Napoleon Dynamite]]''
*: Deb: Well, isn't anyone else here trying to earn money for college?
*: Kip: '''Your mom''' goes to college.

